analyzed_images.image_description:
The image is a map titled "VATSIM Germany Sektor Reutlingen (EDDS_REU_APP)." It is designed for flight simulation use only and is not to be used for real-world flight. The map outlines the airspace sector for Reutlingen, with various zones marked with their respective altitude limits and identifiers.

Key features include:
- The central area labeled "REU1" with an altitude limit of 145 GND.
- Surrounding areas with different altitude limits, such as "REU2" with 145 to 395 GND.
- Various other zones with specific altitude limits, such as "LFST_SIV" (145 GND), "STG1" (145 GND), "DKB2" (245 to 105 GND), and "EDDMFUE" (245 to 105 GND).
- The map includes boundaries and labels for different airspace sectors and their respective altitude limits.

The map is dated 07.01.2022 and is credited to VACC Germany.

The image is a map of the VATSIM Germany sector for Stuttgart (EDDS_STG_APP). It shows various air traffic control sectors and their respective ground (GND) levels. The central sector, labeled STG1, has a ground level of 145. Surrounding sectors include STG2, STG3, STG5, and STG6, each with different ground levels ranging from 75 to 105. Additional sectors such as PFA1, PFA3, PFA4, and others are also indicated with their respective ground levels. The map is dated 07.01.2022 and is provided by VACC Germany. It is intended for flight simulator use only and not for real-world flight operations.

metadata.abstract: The document 'EBG 8 [REU, STG]' provides detailed information for flight simulator use, specifically for the sectors Reutlingen (EDDS REU APP) and Stuttgart (EDDS STG APP) under VATSIM Germany. It includes sector boundaries, frequencies, and callsigns for Langen Radar. The main sector tasks for REU involve handling in- and outbounds from/to the south, as well as traffic to and from EDSB and EDTL. For STG, the primary tasks include managing in- and outbounds from/to the north and traffic to and from EDTY. Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) for both sectors are available at the EDDS SOP. The document emphasizes that it is for flight simulator use only and not for real-world flight.
